Enumeration Type Documentation

enum GtkGraphAnnotationType

Enumerated type to specify the nature of any annotations drawn on a graph

Enumerator:
VERTICAL 

Applies to XY Graphs: a Vertical Annotation line

HORIZONTAL 

Applies to XY Graphs: a Horizontal Annotation line

RADIAL 

Applies to Polar Plots: an Annotation line from the centre to the edge

AZIMUTHAL 

Applies to Polar Plots: a Circular annotation line

VSWR 

Applies to Smith Charts: A Line of constant VSWR

Q 

Applies to Smith Charts: A Line of constant Q

enum GtkGraphAxisType

Enumerated type to specify which axis changes apply to

Enumerator:
GTK_GRAPH_AXIS_INDEPENDANT 

The independant axis of the graph; for XY graphs this is the X-axis, for POLAR graphs this is the angle

GTK_GRAPH_AXIS_DEPENDANT 

The dependant axis of the graph; for XY graphs this is the Y-axis, for POLAR graphs this is the radial distance

enum GtkGraphCrossingType

Enumerated type to specify where one axis should cross the other on an XY graph

Enumerator:
GTK_GRAPH_AXISMAX 

The other axis should cross at the minumum value of this axis

GTK_GRAPH_AXISMIN 

The other axis should cross at the maximum value of this axis

GTK_GRAPH_USERVALUE 

The other axis should cross at a user specified value on this axis

enum GtkGraphLineType

Enumerated type to specify which line should be used to draw a trace

Enumerator:
NO_LINE 

No line

SOLID 

Solid line

DASHED 

Dashed line

DASH_DOT 

Alternate dash-dot line

DOTTED 

Dotted line

LONG_DASH 

Long Dashed line

enum GtkGraphMarkerType

Enumerated type to specify which markers should be used to identify data points on a trace

Enumerator:
GTK_GRAPH_MARKER_NONE 

No marker

GTK_GRAPH_MARKER_SQUARE 

A Square

GTK_GRAPH_MARKER_CIRCLE 

A Circle

GTK_GRAPH_MARKER_DIAMOND 

A Diamond

GTK_GRAPH_MARKER_TRIANGLE 

A Triangle

GTK_GRAPH_MARKER_PLUS 

A Plus (+)

GTK_GRAPH_MARKER_CROSS 

A Cross (X)

GTK_GRAPH_MARKER_STAR 

A Star (*)

enum GtkGraphNumberFormat

Enumerated type to specify how numbers should be displayed

Enumerator:
FLOATING_POINT 

Standard Floating point

ENGINEERING 

Engineering notation (i.e. 1.2E+3) but with exponent always as powers of 3

SCIENTIFIC 

Scientific notation (i.e. 2.7E+4) but with exponent taking any integer value

enum GtkGraphPolarType

Enumerated type to specify radial range of POLAR Graphs

Enumerator:
DEGREES_SYMMETRIC 

Angle measured in degrees from -180 to 180

DEGREES_ANTISYMMETRIC 

Angle measured in degrees from 0 to 360

RADIANS_SYMMETRIC 

Angle measured in radians from -PI to PI

RADIANS_ANTISYMMETRIC 

Angle measured in radians from 0 to 2 PI

enum GtkGraphPosition

Enumerated type to specify legend positions on a graph

Enumerator:
GTK_GRAPH_NORTH_EAST 

Top Edge Centred Horizontally

GTK_GRAPH_EAST 

Top Right Corner

GTK_GRAPH_SOUTH_EAST 

Left Edge Centred Vertically

GTK_GRAPH_SOUTH 

Bottom Right Corner

GTK_GRAPH_SOUTH_WEST 

Bottom Edge Centred Horizontally

GTK_GRAPH_WEST 

Bottom Left Corner

GTK_GRAPH_NORTH_WEST 

Right Edge Centred Vertically

enum GtkGraphType

Enumerated type to specify which type of graph is required

Enumerator:
XY 

An XY (Scatter) graph

POLAR 

A Polar plot

SMITH 

A Smith's Chart

void gtk_graph_smith_set_Z0 ( GtkGraph *  graph,
gfloat  Z0 
)

All Smith's Charts are normalised to a particular impendance (Z0). This function allows the user to normalise the Smith's Chart to a value to something other than the default value of 50 Ohms.

Parameters:
graph the GtkGraph containing the Smiths Chart that you wish to re-normalise
Z0 the new normalisation value
